        },
        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>An <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-ring\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"engagement ring\">engagement ring</a> is not just an accessory, but a symbol of love, commitment and a story you wouldn’t tire talking about even after decades of receiving this proposal ring. It becomes a part of you, like second skin. It silently sits on your finger and reflects light as you move through your everyday habits for a lifetime. Like any fine jewelry, your engagement ring requires care to sparkle for a lifetime. A little care can go a long way and be the reason why it can become an heirloom piece. To protect a diamond ring’s brilliance and to preserve the thoughtful artistry behind a ring, we have curated this blog to cover everything you need to ensure your ring’s shimmer never fades and the ring stays immaculate for decades!<br/><br/></p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qVyerJ": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Proper Ring Care Matters ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Proper Ring Care Matters </h2>",
            "custom_id": "why"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_zyC4LC": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Why_Proper_Ring_Care_Matters.png",
            "text": "<p>Most people assume that once the perfect diamond ring is worn, it is safe indefinitely, especially if you have a sedentary lifestyle with little activity. However, daily wear exposes a diamond proposal ring to various elements that can fade the look or lose the diamond. From lotions to accidental knocks that loosen prongs, to the invisible layers of dust and oil that settle on the ring, there are several reasons why your engagement ring’s brilliance dims. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_tDfwi7": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Proper Ring Paragarph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Most people assume that once the perfect diamond ring is worn, it is safe indefinitely, especially if you have a sedentary lifestyle with little activity. However, daily wear exposes a diamond proposal ring to various elements that can fade the look or lose the diamond. From lotions to accidental knocks that loosen prongs, to the invisible layers of dust and oil that settle on the ring, there are several reasons why your engagement ring’s brilliance dims. </p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_A8fUE6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Daily Habits To Protect Your Engagement Ring ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Daily Habits To Protect Your Engagement Ring </h2><p>Engagement ring care does not have to be complicated. It is easy and with just a few daily habits, you can ensure that your engagement ring stays with you forever without changing. </p>",
            "custom_id": "daily"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_QG3YBN": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Remove it during certain activities ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Remove it during certain activities </h3>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_ry4cQt": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with Text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Remove_it_during_certain_activities.png",
            "text": "<p>Your ring should not be worn during certain activities that are bound to harm the ring’s brilliance or diamond. Any activity that involves high pressure, chemicals or impact that can knock off the diamond, can lead to damage. Some of the activities include swimming, gym, sports, yoga, weight lifting, gardening and even cooking, especially during kneading and marinating food. Some home cleaners have harsh chemicals that can dull the shine of rings as well. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_FpjwHt": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Remove it during Paragragh",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Some ring settings leave the diamond exposed and even a small accidental knock can loosen the stone or bend the prong. Removing your exquisite diamond rings that mean so much to you can help preserve the ring’s shine and save you from unnecessary risks. </p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bhGzpc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Avoid touching the diamond too often",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Avoid touching the diamond too often</h3>",
            "custom_id": "clarity"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_BiE3eV": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with Text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Avoid_touching_the_diamond_too_often.png",
            "text": "<p>We often have the habit to fidget with our unique diamond engagement rings while thinking too hard or when we are emotionally anxious or missing our soulmate. It is tempting to admire the ring and touch it, but our natural oils from our fingertips can add a layer which can also dull the diamond’s shine. This same layer can attract dust, furthering the fadeness.   </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_mEE3FU": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Keep it away from lotions and perfumes ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Keep it away from lotions and perfumes </h3>",
            "custom_id": "carat"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_XgNzg9": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with Text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Keep_it_away_from_lotions_and_perfumes.png",
            "text": "<p>Skincare and beauty products leave residue on the edges of the ring and cloud the diamond, slowly affecting the ring. While the impact may not be visible soon, in the long run, the beauty of the diamond fades because of these lotions and perfumes. This is why we recommend the ‘last on, first off’ rule, which essentially suggests that you put on the ring at the last after getting entirely ready and take it off before you get ready for bed. A few seconds of this care and maintenance can ensure that your diamond keeps shining like its new! </p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_G3AYDN": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How To Clean Your Engagement Ring At Home ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>How To Clean Your Engagement Ring At Home </h2>",
            "custom_id": "how"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_h9TcpQ": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How To Clean Your Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Cleaning your ring at home is both safe and effective when done properly. A single weekly care routine can maintain brilliance with professional cleanings just twice a year to increase the longevity of your ring. </p><p>Follow this simple and gentle method:</p><ol><li>Prepare a bowl of lukewarm (not hot/not cold) water</li><li>Add 2-3 drops of MILD dish soap or more preferably, a jewelry cleaning liquid</li><li>Let the ring soak for approximately half an hour</li><li>Gently clean the ring around the grooves with a soft bristled brush </li><li>Rinse around warm running water</li><li>Wipe it clean with a lint-free cloth, such as the one Lucira provides along with the ring’s packaging. </li></ol><p>Tip: Save a scary incident of losing your ring in the sink by placing a strainer in advance in case the ring slips from your hand while rinsing! </p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BhW7hB": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How To Clean Your Paragraph2 ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>What to Avoid </h3><p>Knowing what NOT to do is very important while taking care of your best engagement rings. </p><p>You must avoid harsh chemicals such as acetone, a key ingredient in many nail polish removers. These chemicals can discolor<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings-yellow-gold\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" gold diamond rings\"> gold diamond rings</a> for women over a period of time. While jewelers have specialized ultrasonic machines for cleaning, household ultrasonic cleaners can be very risky. The vibrations can loosen the stone, especially if the diamond is set delicately in a pave or halo setting. Other remedies such as toothpaste and baking soda as cleaning agents can also be harsh on the diamond’s surface and metal. </p><h3>Lucira Tip</h3><p>At<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" Lucira Jewelry\"> Lucira Jewelry</a>, we recommend you doing a regular ‘sparkle check.’ Hold your ring under natural sunlight and rotate it slowly. </p><p>‘Does the diamond catch the light with the same intensity?’</p><p>‘Do the prongs sit firmly and symmetrically?’</p><p>If anything seems off, take the ring to a professional. This simple routine helps you detect any major repairs later. </p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_6HcmaG": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Professional Maintenance and Inspections ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Professional Maintenance and Inspections  </h2>",
            "custom_id": "professional"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_NUyD9B": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Professional_Maintenance_and_Inspections.png",
            "text": "<p>No amount of home care can replace professional inspections. It is recommended to get professional inspection once a year and professional cleaning twice a year. During inspections, jewelers check everything in place - literally. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_jUDqfe": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Professional  Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>They tighten any loosened prongs, polish the metal, deep clean the ring using safe methods, check for any weakened settings and ensure no diamonds are shifting. Think of it as a regular health check-up for your engagement ring.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_fmB9QF": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How to Store Your Engagement Ring Safely",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>How to Store Your Engagement Ring Safely</h2>",
            "custom_id": "how-to"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_Di8yJD": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/How_to_Store_Your_Engagement_Ring_Safely.png",
            "text": "<p>Sometimes you’ll need to take off your ring during skincare routines, workouts, and travel. It is important to store the engagement ring safely to avoid any scratches or exposure to moisture. One of the best ways to store your engagement ring is a jewelry pouch with soft inner lining or a box with separate compartments so that your ring doesn’t scratch against other jewelry.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Uiypc6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How to Store Your Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p> It's best to store your engagement ring in a cool, dry place which is away from any sunlight and a space with minimal exposure to humidity. </p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_9LDfB8": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Conclusion",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Conclusion</h2><p>Your engagement ring is a promise etched into stone, crafted with care to last a lifetime. With the right care, the beauty sustains, with years of togetherness reflecting in the ring’s brilliance as the years pass by and memories are created. By incorporating simple habits of do’s and don’ts to care for your ring, you ensure that your ring receives the love it deserves and the brilliance shines the way the ring was crafted to show. </p>",
            "custom_id": "conclusion"
          }
        }
      },
